Diagnosis:
Body size and maculation pattern of this species is variable, but this species can be identified by the following combination of characters: female, T6 strongly concave in profile (
Fig. 25f
); male, lateral protuberances on T2–T3 covered by distinct yellowish-white tufts (
Fig. 26d
), apical process of S8 broadly triangular (
Fig. 26h
), lateral spine of T5 black (
Fig. 26a
, 
Fig. 26e
).

